2807	/* Free a module string object obtained with one of the Redis modules API calls
2808	 * that return new string objects.
2809	 *
2810	 * It is possible to call this function even when automatic memory management
2811	 * is enabled. In that case the string will be released ASAP and removed
2812	 * from the pool of string to release at the end.
2813	 *
2814	 * If the string was created with a NULL context 'ctx', it is also possible to
2815	 * pass ctx as NULL when releasing the string (but passing a context will not
2816	 * create any issue). Strings created with a context should be freed also passing
2817	 * the context, so if you want to free a string out of context later, make sure
2818	 * to create it using a NULL context.
