3921	/* Return the current context's flags. The flags provide information on the
3922	 * current request context (whether the client is a Lua script or in a MULTI),
3923	 * and about the Redis instance in general, i.e replication and persistence.
3924	 *
3925	 * It is possible to call this function even with a NULL context, however
3926	 * in this case the following flags will not be reported:
3927	 *
3928	 *  * LUA, MULTI, REPLICATED, DIRTY (see below for more info).
3929	 *
3930	 * Available flags and their meaning:
3931	 *
3932	 *  * REDISMODULE_CTX_FLAGS_LUA: The command is running in a Lua script
3933	 *
3934	 *  * REDISMODULE_CTX_FLAGS_MULTI: The command is running inside a transaction
3935	 *
3936	 *  * REDISMODULE_CTX_FLAGS_REPLICATED: The command was sent over the replication
3937	 *    link by the MASTER
3938	 *
3939	 *  * REDISMODULE_CTX_FLAGS_MASTER: The Redis instance is a master
3940	 *
3941	 *  * REDISMODULE_CTX_FLAGS_SLAVE: The Redis instance is a slave
3942	 *
3943	 *  * REDISMODULE_CTX_FLAGS_READONLY: The Redis instance is read-only
3944	 *
3945	 *  * REDISMODULE_CTX_FLAGS_CLUSTER: The Redis instance is in cluster mode
3946	 *
3947	 *  * REDISMODULE_CTX_FLAGS_AOF: The Redis instance has AOF enabled
3948	 *
3949	 *  * REDISMODULE_CTX_FLAGS_RDB: The instance has RDB enabled
3950	 *
3951	 *  * REDISMODULE_CTX_FLAGS_MAXMEMORY:  The instance has Maxmemory set
3952	 *
3953	 *  * REDISMODULE_CTX_FLAGS_EVICT:  Maxmemory is set and has an eviction
