7988	/* Add a new element to the digest. This function can be called multiple times
7989	 * one element after the other, for all the elements that constitute a given
7990	 * data structure. The function call must be followed by the call to
7991	 * `RedisModule_DigestEndSequence` eventually, when all the elements that are
7992	 * always in a given order are added. See the Redis Modules data types
7993	 * documentation for more info. However this is a quick example that uses Redis
7994	 * data types as an example.
7995	 *
7996	 * To add a sequence of unordered elements (for example in the case of a Redis
7997	 * Set), the pattern to use is:
7998	 *
7999	 *     foreach element {

5000	    server.shutdown_mstime = 0;
5001	    atomicSet(server.last_sig_received, 0);
5002	    replyToClientsBlockedOnShutdown();
5003	    unpauseActions(PAUSE_DURING_SHUTDOWN);
5004	}
