2396	/* Load a Redis object of the specified type from the specified file.
2397	 * On success a newly allocated object is returned, otherwise NULL.
2398	 *
2399	 * error - When the function returns NULL and if 'error' is not NULL, the
2400	 *   integer pointed by 'error' is set to the type of error that occurred
2401	 * minExpiredField - If loading a hash with expiration on fields, then this value
2402	 *   will be set to the minimum expire time found in the hash fields. If there are
2403	 *   no fields with expiration or it is not a hash, then it will set be to
2404	 *   EB_EXPIRE_TIME_INVALID.
